Requirements:

Computer with at least 8 GB RAM (16 GB preferred)
Virtualization software (VMware Workstation, VirtualBox)
Kali Linux VM (attacker machine)
Metasploitable VM (target machine)

Setup:

Install Virtualization Software: Download and install VMware Workstation or VirtualBox.
Download VMs:
Kali Linux: Kali Linux Download
Metasploitable: Metasploitable Download
Configure Network: Set both VMs to use a host-only or internal network.
Launch VMs: Start both the Kali Linux and Metasploitable VMs.
